						<summary>

						<p>On the fourth pillar of the <hi rend="italic">maṇḍapa</hi> in front of the Vēdāraṇyēśvara temple.</p>						

						<p>Parāntaka I. Year 1[8]: 925 A.D.</p>						

						<p>The details of date, <hi rend="italic">viz.</hi>, Makara, Monday, and Śoti and Saṅkrānti are irregular. </p>						

						<p>This inscription records the gift of 90 sheep, by Māṉinakka-pirāṭṭiyār, wife of Śembiyaṉ Mūvēndavēḷār <hi rend="italic">alias</hi> Śāttaṉ Ulagaṉ of Vaṇḍāḻañjēri in Niṉṟayūr-nāḍu for burning a perpetual lamp to the deity with one <hi rend="italic">uḻakku</hi> of ghee by the measure <hi rend="italic">Tirumaṟaikkāḍaṉ.</hi></p>						

						</summary>
